==English==

===Noun==
'''MPTP''' 
# 1-methyl-4-phenyl-1,2,3,6-tetrahydropyridine
# A byproduct of synthetic [[heroin]], or [[MPPP]], which causes Parkinsonian symptoms in users
# A [[neurotoxin]] which degrades into [[MPP]]+ after crossing the [[blood brain barrier]], which causes a degredation of the [[dopaminergic]] neurons within the [[substantia nigra]]

==Quotes==
*'''2005 Dec 29''' Petzinger, et al. ''Journal of Neuroscience Research''
*:The neurotoxicant 1-methyl-4-phenyl-1,2,3,6-tetrahydropyridine '''MPTP''' provides an excellent opportunity to study repair and response to injury in the basal ganglia.